{
  "text": "To our knowledge this is the first study to calculate the costs to women of different tests in the DS screening pathway. Henderson et al. reported that the costs to women of antenatal ultrasound screening in 2002 were \u00a312.42 [CITATION_1] . When we inflate these costs to 2013/14 (approximately \u00a320), they are similar to the costs we found for NIPT, but lower than the costs for DS screening (which may include an ultrasound scan and also phlebotomy).",
